[[Eshell]] is a shell written in EmacsLisp. It is included as of Emacs 21.

Eshell was written by JohnWiegley, and later maintained by [[aidalgol|Aidan Gauland]].

== Categories ==

== Manual ==

* [http://www.gnu.org/software/emacs/manual/html_mono/eshell.html The Eshell manual] ([http://git.savannah.gnu.org/cgit/emacs.git/tree/doc/misc/eshell.texi TexInfo source])
* [http://git.savannah.gnu.org/cgit/emacs.git/tree/lisp/eshell Source code] (`M-x find-library eshell RET')

=== General Usage ===
* [EshellAlias Aliases] -- Alias ##open## to ##open-file## etc.
* [EshellFunctions Functions] -- Writing functions in Eshell
* [EshellForLoop For Loops] -- Writing loops like ##for x in a b c do ...##
* [EshellGlobbing Globbing] -- Expanding wildcards such as ##*.txt##
* [EshellAutojump Auto-Jump] -- use `j' to jump to your favorite directories
* [EshellBackticks Backticks] -- Replace a command in ##`backticks`## with its output.


=== Interfacing with Other Modes ===
* EshellAndAngeFtp -- using eshell on remote hosts
* EshellAndEmacsServer -- Use eshell like a shell in a terminal-emulator
* EshellAndTramp -- using eshell with tramp
* EshellAndViper -- making Eshell and Viper play well together
* EshellScreen -- make eshell interact with GNU screen
* EshellVisualCommands -- starting certain commands in AnsiTerm
* EshellAndPdbTrack -- how to make PdbTrack work with Eshell
* EshellInteractivelyRemove
* Eshell And DiredMode -- using [[Eshell]] to read directories for [[dired]]: Customize variable `eshell-ls-use-in-dired'

=== Themes and Customization ===
* EshellColor -- faces, escape sequences, etc.
* EshellCompletion
* EshellPrompt -- changing your prompt

=== About Eshell ===
* EshellHistory and EshellDirectoryHistory
* EshellWishList -- wish list and questions.
* EshellManual -- commentary and Texinfo source for the first edition of the manual (c. 2000).
* EshellElDoc -- ElDoc functionality for Eshell


=== Extending Eshell ===
* EshellEnhancedLS -- RET- and mouse-sensitive `ls' for Eshell
* EshellExtensions
* EshellBmk -- integration between Eshell and [[bookmark]]s
* EshellScrolling -- make eshell scroll to the bottom of the screen
* EshellWThirtyTwo -- snippets that make a w32 user's day brighter
* EshellControlFromOtherBuffer
* EshellIndicator
* EshellLnkFileSupport -- support for Windows shortcut
* EshellRedirection -- redirecting to files, to buffers and to the clipboard
* EshellMultipleEshellBuffers -- Makes having multiple eshells open/cycling between them easier
* EshellNavigation
* [https://github.com/dieggsy/esh-autosuggest esh-autosuggest] Fish-like autosuggestion.
* [https://github.com/LemonBreezes/emacs-fish-completion emacs-fish-completion] Fish completion for Emacs and Eshell.

